
[README]

    The javascript files has been used and tested with node.js v14.16.0

    npm module installed:

        $ npm install kraken-api




[CONFIGURATION]

    In order to communicate with the kraken API: 

    Set the KEY and SECRET token inside the "api-key.json" file.


[USE]

    run kraken.sh and follow the instruction --help


[NOTE]

    Inside the file "assets.json" are present all assets available from kraken.

    When requesting, some pair are considered query_unkown from kraken.   